name: 5-methylbenzoxazole
Reason: 5-methylbenzoxazole has a melting point that can be predicted by considering its structural components. The basic unit for comparison is benzene, which has a melting point of 5.5°C. The methyl group introduces a rigid structure, which can participate in hydrogen bonding and increase the melting point by approximately +5°C. The oxazole ring introduces additional rigidity, estimated at around +20°C. The presence of two carbonyl groups can also contribute to the melting point, estimated at around +20°C each.
